---
import Specimen from '@/layouts/Specimen.astro'
import { BackgroundImage, Image } from '@splendidlabz/astro'
---

<Specimen
  title="Background images"
  lede="Two ways to optimize background images: an inline background-image property, or a real image with object-fit: cover."
  code="src/pages/background-images.astro"
>
  <h2>Using an inline background-image property</h2>
  <p>
    <code>BackgroundImage</code> optimizes the image with
    <code>getImage</code> and writes it into the CSS
    <code>background-image</code> property.
  </p>
  <BackgroundImage class="rounded-lg overflow-hidden" src="/src/assets/hero.jpg">
    <div class="vertical gap-2 text-white" style="padding: 3rem">
      <h3 class="text-white">Background image</h3>
      <p>The content sets the height. The image covers the space behind it.</p>
    </div>
  </BackgroundImage>

  <h2>Using a real image with object-fit: cover</h2>
  <p>
    The better experience: a real <code>picture</code> with
    <code>srcset</code>, overlaid with content in a
    <code>stack</code>. <code>backgroundMode</code> pins the image to fill the
    stack.
  </p>
  <div class="stack rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <Image src="/src/assets/background.png" alt="" backgroundMode />
    <div class="vertical gap-2" style="padding: 3rem">
      <h3>Real image behind content</h3>
      <p>
        Browsers still get modern formats and pick the right size from
        <code>srcset</code>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Specimen>
